1
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,000
=Our Days=

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,720
(Adapted from Lang Lang's original novel
"The Prime of the Goddess")

3
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,160
=Episode 17=

4
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:38,979
Mom?

5
00:01:39,619 --> 00:01:40,540
What are you doing here?

6
00:01:41,699 --> 00:01:42,859
What's going on?

7
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:44,580
Don't!

8
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:45,619
Lie down.

9
00:01:46,460 --> 00:01:47,660
I would have no idea that you were

10
00:01:47,699 --> 00:01:48,219
hospitalized

11
00:01:48,219 --> 00:01:49,699
had Qian Feng not called me.

12
00:01:50,059 --> 00:01:51,100
What's going on?

13
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:52,300
I'm fine.

14
00:01:55,699 --> 00:01:56,900
Why is your face injured too?

15
00:01:57,020 --> 00:01:57,619
I...

16
00:01:58,419 --> 00:01:59,100
I'm fine.

17
00:01:59,219 --> 00:02:00,740
How did you get injured?

18
00:02:01,779 --> 00:02:03,180
My goodness. What happened?

19
00:02:03,499 --> 00:02:04,419
Where are you going?

20
00:02:06,540 --> 00:02:07,259
I'm going to work.

21
00:02:08,219 --> 00:02:09,059
You can't just leave him.

22
00:02:09,059 --> 00:02:10,659
He needs someone to look after him.

23
00:02:11,059 --> 00:02:12,099
Go and apply for leave.

24
00:02:12,420 --> 00:02:13,499
I can't.

25
00:02:17,779 --> 00:02:19,460
You can't expect me to tend to him

26
00:02:19,460 --> 00:02:20,900
when I'm this old.

27
00:02:22,539 --> 00:02:24,020
I'll hire a caretaker for him.

28
00:02:24,779 --> 00:02:26,020
He doesn't need a caretaker.

29
00:02:26,339 --> 00:02:27,300
You're his wife.

30
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:28,700
He needs you.

31
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:31,819
We're divorced.

32
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:32,939
I'm not obliged to do so.

33
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:35,379
Have you completed the procedure?

34
00:02:36,860 --> 00:02:38,140
You haven't, right?

35
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:39,099
That means you're obliged to do so.

36
00:02:40,619 --> 00:02:41,260
Enough already.

37
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:42,099
I'm not a vegetarian, you know?

38
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:42,860
I can do it myself.

39
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:43,499
Don't talk.

40
00:02:44,659 --> 00:02:45,260
Have some water.

41
00:02:45,260 --> 00:02:45,819
No thanks.

42
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:47,180
You should.
Look at how dry your lips are.

43
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:47,900
Hurry. Be obedient.

44
00:02:50,059 --> 00:02:50,740
Xiang Zhong,

45
00:02:52,219 --> 00:02:54,140
if you wish to continue with
the divorce procedure,

46
00:02:54,819 --> 00:02:56,020
you have to take care

47
00:02:56,059 --> 00:02:57,059
of Deng Haiyang.

48
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:58,020
If not,

49
00:02:58,980 --> 00:03:00,379
I would never agree to the divorce.

50
00:03:02,020 --> 00:03:03,900
You don't get to make the call here.

51
00:03:05,659 --> 00:03:07,140
She's something else now.
Did you see that?

52
00:03:07,260 --> 00:03:08,180
She's something else.

53
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:09,580
Look at how arrogant you look.

54
00:03:09,819 --> 00:03:10,539
You merely hired

55
00:03:10,659 --> 00:03:12,020
a divorce attorney in Shanghai,
you know?

56
00:03:13,379 --> 00:03:14,339
Great timing.

57
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:15,740
You can ask the attorney about this.

58
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:17,180
You're having an affair outside

59
00:03:17,339 --> 00:03:18,539
even when the divorce procedure
isn't completed.

60
00:03:18,619 --> 00:03:19,659
What should we do about that, then?

61
00:03:20,260 --> 00:03:21,619
How would the verdict go

62
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:22,980
if we were to go to court?

63
00:03:23,140 --> 00:03:23,860
Mom!

64
00:03:24,779 --> 00:03:26,819
Where did you hear that nonsense from?

65
00:03:27,619 --> 00:03:28,539
Listen,

66
00:03:29,020 --> 00:03:30,059
good news travels near

67
00:03:30,499 --> 00:03:32,219
while bad news travels far.

68
00:03:33,740 --> 00:03:34,300
Fine.

69
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:35,379
Xiang Zhong,

70
00:03:35,580 --> 00:03:36,339
since we're already

71
00:03:36,339 --> 00:03:37,099
talking about this topic,

72
00:03:37,140 --> 00:03:38,140
let's make things clear.

73
00:03:39,819 --> 00:03:40,619
You want to get a divorce?

74
00:03:41,619 --> 00:03:42,260
Sure.

75
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:43,939
The conditions are simple.

76
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:44,860
You have

77
00:03:45,059 --> 00:03:45,900
to walk away empty-handed,

78
00:03:46,099 --> 00:03:47,339
leave the house behind for Haiyang,

79
00:03:47,659 --> 00:03:48,619
and pay us an extra one million yuan

80
00:03:48,659 --> 00:03:49,740
as a mental damage compensation.

81
00:03:51,779 --> 00:03:52,659
What gives?

82
00:03:52,819 --> 00:03:53,499
What gives?

83
00:03:54,499 --> 00:03:56,020
He's lying on the hospital bed.

84
00:03:56,819 --> 00:03:57,819
This will definitely affect

85
00:03:57,819 --> 00:03:59,140
his quality of life.

86
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:01,659
My shinbone is fractured.

87
00:04:01,939 --> 00:04:03,659
How will this affect my quality of life?

88
00:04:03,659 --> 00:04:04,099
My goodness.

89
00:04:04,099 --> 00:04:05,580
That's enough.

90
00:04:05,580 --> 00:04:06,740
She already turned you into a cuckold.

91
00:04:06,819 --> 00:04:08,140
Why are you still defending her?

92
00:04:08,219 --> 00:04:09,580
I'll say this as well.

93
00:04:09,819 --> 00:04:10,740
We will get a divorce.

94
00:04:10,939 --> 00:04:12,260
You won't get a single cent from me.

95
00:04:12,539 --> 00:04:13,619
My parents bought the house for me.

96
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:14,339
Don't even think about it.

97
00:04:14,619 --> 00:04:15,379
Stop right there!

98
00:04:16,219 --> 00:04:16,820
Stop right there!

99
00:04:17,140 --> 00:04:18,500
Listen up!

100
00:04:18,739 --> 00:04:19,659
I won't let you

101
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:20,940
take all the benefits!

102
00:04:20,940 --> 00:04:22,260
You won't get away that easily!

103
00:04:22,299 --> 00:04:23,859
Can you please stop?

104
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:25,020
Just shut up!

105
00:04:33,820 --> 00:04:34,580
Xiang?

106
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:36,099
Xiang!

107
00:04:36,739 --> 00:04:37,380
Hurry!

108
00:04:39,539 --> 00:04:40,539
Xiang Zhong's mother-in-law
is calling us.

109
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:41,940
Just answer the call, then.

110
00:04:42,020 --> 00:04:43,260
I can't communicate with her.

111
00:04:43,539 --> 00:04:44,060
You're not answering it?

112
00:04:44,179 --> 00:04:45,700
How can I talk to her, then?

113
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:46,580
Just tell her.

114
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:48,020
It's been ringing for so long. Hurry.

115
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:48,820
Talk to her.

116
00:04:51,380 --> 00:04:52,620
Hello, In-law.

117
00:04:53,099 --> 00:04:53,739
Xiang Zhijun,

118
00:04:54,099 --> 00:04:55,659
tell Xiang Zhong to come
to the hospital right now.

119
00:04:56,859 --> 00:04:58,140
Bai, what's going on?

120
00:04:58,339 --> 00:04:59,419
What do you mean?

121
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,060
Deng Haiyang broke his leg.

122
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:02,099
He's been hospitalized.

123
00:05:02,299 --> 00:05:03,620
Don't you think
Xiang Zhong should be here?

124
00:05:04,179 --> 00:05:05,500
Tell her this.

125
00:05:05,859 --> 00:05:07,500
She has to come and take care of him

126
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:08,940
as long as
the divorce procedure isn't completed.

127
00:05:10,659 --> 00:05:11,739
Hello, Bai?

128
00:05:12,419 --> 00:05:13,020
She hung up.

129
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:15,380
How did he break his leg?

130
00:05:15,739 --> 00:05:16,940
How should I know?

131
00:05:17,659 --> 00:05:18,380
What about this?

132
00:05:19,339 --> 00:05:20,099
Let's prepare some food

133
00:05:20,739 --> 00:05:21,460
tomorrow.

134
00:05:22,539 --> 00:05:23,500
Tell Xiang Zhong to come.

135
00:05:23,940 --> 00:05:24,620
We'll visit Haiyang

136
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:25,620
in the hospital together.

137
00:05:26,299 --> 00:05:27,140
Tomorrow?

138
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:29,260
But he's already hospitalized.

139
00:05:30,339 --> 00:05:31,299
Don't worry.

140
00:05:32,020 --> 00:05:33,419
Do you think his mother

141
00:05:33,620 --> 00:05:34,539
has the time to call us

142
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:35,380
if his life was in danger?

143
00:05:36,219 --> 00:05:37,539
You're always smarter than me.

144
00:05:43,219 --> 00:05:43,859
Why did you come

145
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:45,140
and pick me up all of a sudden?

146
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:47,779
What do you mean by that?

147
00:05:48,539 --> 00:05:50,620
You were in a major meeting.
I was worried that you might be drunk.

148
00:05:53,419 --> 00:05:54,940
What's that smell?

149
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,099
It's so fragrant.

150
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:00,539
Do you mean the fragrance?

151
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:03,900
Do you still remember Sun Ying?

152
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:06,299
Which Sun Ying?

153
00:06:06,460 --> 00:06:07,859
You mean the one who went to Shenzhen
on your behalf?

154
00:06:09,659 --> 00:06:12,140
She criticized the team she was once on

155
00:06:12,339 --> 00:06:14,620
severely.

156
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:19,140
It must've been tough on you.

157
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:22,260
The scent is too strong.

158
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,260
Did you change the fragrance?

159
00:06:24,779 --> 00:06:25,700
I didn't.

160
00:06:28,779 --> 00:06:29,900
This doesn't smell like

161
00:06:29,940 --> 00:06:30,620
the previous one.

162
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,620
I can't take it

163
00:06:31,659 --> 00:06:32,859
when the flower scent is too strong.

164
00:06:33,140 --> 00:06:34,140
This is too much.

165
00:06:36,539 --> 00:06:37,460
It's not that bad.

166
00:06:37,859 --> 00:06:38,859
They smell almost the same.

167
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:01,339
Gao Ping, Xiang Qian,

168
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:02,419
you guys are back.

169
00:07:02,859 --> 00:07:03,700
Yeah.

170
00:07:06,739 --> 00:07:08,380
Why are you here this early?

171
00:07:08,580 --> 00:07:09,419
I told her to come.

172
00:07:09,580 --> 00:07:10,500
I've been too busy lately.

173
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:11,900
I told her to proofread my thesis.

174
00:07:12,739 --> 00:07:14,219
Once I'm done with the thesis,

175
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:15,219
I'll play with

176
00:07:15,260 --> 00:07:16,339
Qi and Cong

177
00:07:16,419 --> 00:07:17,339
and teach them how to
make things with modeling clay.

178
00:07:18,779 --> 00:07:20,460
You're exploiting labor here.

179
00:07:20,779 --> 00:07:21,500
That's not true.

180
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,299
Gao Ping gave me

181
00:07:23,299 --> 00:07:24,260
an opportunity to learn.

182
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:26,979
I'll continue, then.

183
00:07:27,020 --> 00:07:27,779
Go ahead.

184
00:07:28,140 --> 00:07:28,700
Ping,

185
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,060
I'm heating milk with the microwave.

186
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,820
You and Xiang Qian can share it.

187
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:34,460
Alright. Leave it there. I'll get it.

188
00:07:43,820 --> 00:07:44,500
What's wrong?

189
00:07:45,380 --> 00:07:46,020
What's wrong?

190
00:07:46,260 --> 00:07:46,779
What's wrong?

191
00:07:46,779 --> 00:07:47,179
I'm fine.

192
00:07:47,179 --> 00:07:48,060
It scalded my hand.

193
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:48,580
I'm fine.

194
00:07:49,020 --> 00:07:49,659
My goodness.

195
00:07:50,020 --> 00:07:51,219
Don't touch it.

196
00:07:51,219 --> 00:07:51,820
I'll do it.

197
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:53,380
Don't pick it up with your hands.

198
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:54,339
Stay out of this. Just leave.

199
00:07:54,460 --> 00:07:55,020
I'll do it.

200
00:07:56,739 --> 00:07:58,179
I told you not to do that.

201
00:07:58,339 --> 00:07:59,219
You just had to do it, huh?

202
00:07:59,219 --> 00:08:00,060
Aunty, please clean it.

203
00:08:00,099 --> 00:08:01,020
I'm fine.

204
00:08:04,060 --> 00:08:05,339
Gao Ping, hurry and treat your wound.

205
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:06,299
I'm fine.

206
00:08:10,659 --> 00:08:12,260
Xiang Qian, what else do you need?

207
00:08:14,779 --> 00:08:15,659
Sit down.

208
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:21,539
Do you know how old you are?

209
00:08:27,739 --> 00:08:28,779
I just went and got changed

210
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:30,179
as it's almost time
to pick the children up.

211
00:08:30,779 --> 00:08:31,539
Look at you.

212
00:08:31,939 --> 00:08:33,340
Aunty, let me help you out.

213
00:08:33,740 --> 00:08:34,980
It's fine. I'll clean it.

214
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:36,340
It's fine. Pass me

215
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:37,459
the broom. I'll help you out.

216
00:08:37,539 --> 00:08:38,819
I'm fine. The cut isn't deep.

217
00:08:39,419 --> 00:08:40,179
You should go now.

218
00:08:40,819 --> 00:08:41,860
Be careful, okay?

219
00:08:50,140 --> 00:08:51,740
Did you scald yourself as well?

220
00:08:52,539 --> 00:08:53,179
I'm fine.

221
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:56,140
Disinfect it and let it air out for now.

222
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:57,980
Let's see if there are
any blisters later.

223
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:15,179
Don't you think Li Shu is too familiar

224
00:09:15,539 --> 00:09:16,779
with our house's layout?

225
00:09:18,699 --> 00:09:19,779
What? Do you feel uncomfortable

226
00:09:19,779 --> 00:09:20,539
just because she knew

227
00:09:20,620 --> 00:09:21,779
where to find the band-aid?

228
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:24,620
She helped Aunty treat her wound

229
00:09:24,740 --> 00:09:26,059
when she cut herself last time.

230
00:09:26,740 --> 00:09:27,500
I think she's just

231
00:09:27,579 --> 00:09:28,659
too warm-hearted.

232
00:09:29,779 --> 00:09:31,260
It's not about being warm-hearted.

233
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:34,380
Don't you think
that she's acting strange?

234
00:09:37,299 --> 00:09:37,900
She's not that bad.

235
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:39,220
She's just a little too warm-hearted.

236
00:09:39,299 --> 00:09:39,819
It's...

237
00:09:45,299 --> 00:09:46,699
Share her WeChat profile with me, then.

238
00:09:47,819 --> 00:09:49,059
What? Do you have business with her?

239
00:09:50,140 --> 00:09:51,220
She's my children's teacher.

240
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:52,740
What's wrong with me
asking for her WeChat profile?

241
00:09:54,620 --> 00:09:55,500
I'm fine with it

242
00:09:55,579 --> 00:09:56,740
if you want to ask her about

243
00:09:56,819 --> 00:09:57,740
our children's studies.

244
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,459
But if you intend

245
00:09:59,579 --> 00:10:00,740
to ask about my relationship with her,

246
00:10:01,419 --> 00:10:03,059
I'll tell you this first.

247
00:10:03,579 --> 00:10:04,779
I care about this family a lot.

248
00:10:04,939 --> 00:10:06,220
I care about Cong and Qi a lot as well.

249
00:10:06,459 --> 00:10:07,939
Please don't be so paranoid

250
00:10:08,459 --> 00:10:09,620
and sensitive.

251
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:14,179
I think you should

252
00:10:14,179 --> 00:10:15,500
care about how sensitive I am.

253
00:10:51,579 --> 00:10:53,100
Is Xiang Qian causing you trouble again?

254
00:10:54,939 --> 00:10:56,539
I shared your WeChat profile
to Xiang Qian.

255
00:10:58,179 --> 00:10:59,620
Do I have to approve her friend request?

256
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,659
You have no reason not to.

257
00:11:07,059 --> 00:11:07,819
Don't worry.

258
00:11:07,980 --> 00:11:10,260
I don't post anything on my Moments.

259
00:11:17,579 --> 00:11:18,380
This is for you.

260
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:22,860
You can't just

261
00:11:23,340 --> 00:11:24,819
borrow the ring
from your friend all the time.

262
00:11:25,459 --> 00:11:26,100
You're wearing it for one moment

263
00:11:26,179 --> 00:11:27,140
and not wearing the next.

264
00:11:27,459 --> 00:11:28,779
It'll be strange
if people ask you about it.

265
00:11:31,419 --> 00:11:32,500
This is my first time receiving

266
00:11:32,579 --> 00:11:33,980
a ring from a man.

267
00:11:36,699 --> 00:11:39,140
Say, do you think I should be happy

268
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:41,100
or upset?

269
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:46,500
Help me put it on.

270
00:12:36,779 --> 00:12:37,380
Xiang Nan,

271
00:12:37,939 --> 00:12:38,539
where are you?

272
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:39,980
I'm in the studio.

273
00:12:41,539 --> 00:12:43,659
Jiaqiao is going to meet Li Hao today.

274
00:12:44,260 --> 00:12:45,500
You should keep her company

275
00:12:46,059 --> 00:12:47,260
so that you can keep Jiaqiao in check.

276
00:12:48,299 --> 00:12:49,100
I can't be there today.

277
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:50,220
I'm very busy today.

278
00:12:50,459 --> 00:12:51,419
You have two other friends

279
00:12:51,459 --> 00:12:52,459
helping you out, right?

280
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:53,459
You have no idea

281
00:12:53,459 --> 00:12:55,020
how genuine Li Hao is.

282
00:12:55,779 --> 00:12:56,860
He fainted

283
00:12:56,980 --> 00:12:58,059
at the construction site

284
00:12:58,539 --> 00:12:59,579
